1
00:02:27,599 --> 00:02:29,719
I hear they might promote Bryukhanov.

2
00:02:30,839 --> 00:02:33,879
This little problem we have
with the safety test,

3
00:02:34,679 --> 00:02:37,079
if it's completed successfully...

4
00:02:38,359 --> 00:02:40,999
Yes, I think promotion's very likely.

5
00:02:41,999 --> 00:02:43,919
Who knows, maybe Moscow.

6
00:02:45,839 --> 00:02:48,119
Naturally, they'll put me in charge
once he's gone,

7
00:02:48,199 --> 00:02:50,839
and then I'll need someone
to take my old job.

8
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:54,719
I could pick Sitnikov.

9
00:03:03,199 --> 00:03:04,919
I would like to be considered.

10
00:03:08,439 --> 00:03:09,758
We'll keep that in mind.

11
00:03:11,599 --> 00:03:15,559
Viktor Petrovich, preparations
for the test have gone smoothly.

12
00:03:15,638 --> 00:03:18,798
Comrade Dyatlov's been working
per my instructions,

13
00:03:18,879 --> 00:03:22,199
and Reactor 4 output's been
reduced to 1,600 megawatts.

14
00:03:23,039 --> 00:03:26,198
With your approval, we're ready
to continue lowering power to...

15
00:03:26,279 --> 00:03:27,399
We have to wait.

16
00:03:28,999 --> 00:03:29,959
Is, uh...

17
00:03:30,519 --> 00:03:32,879
Are you going to ask me
if there's a problem, Nikolai?

18
00:03:33,319 --> 00:03:35,079
You can't read a fucking face?

19
00:03:35,639 --> 00:03:37,919
Three years,
I've tried to finish this test.

20
00:03:37,998 --> 00:03:39,079
Three years.

21
00:03:46,238 --> 00:03:48,359
I've just had a call from
the grid controller in Kiev.

22
00:03:48,438 --> 00:03:50,519
He says we can't
lower power any further,

23
00:03:50,599 --> 00:03:51,839
not for another 10 hours.

24
00:03:51,919 --> 00:03:53,679
A grid controller?
Where does he get off...

25
00:03:53,759 --> 00:03:56,279
It's not the grid controller's
decision, Dyatlov.

26
00:03:57,399 --> 00:03:58,679
It's the end of the month.

27
00:03:59,439 --> 00:04:02,079
All the productivity quotas.

28
00:04:02,159 --> 00:04:04,758
Everyone's working overtime.
The factories need power.

29
00:04:04,839 --> 00:04:06,518
Someone's pushing down from above.

30
00:04:06,599 --> 00:04:08,079
Not that we'll never know who.

31
00:04:16,398 --> 00:04:18,559
So, do we have to scrap it or what?

32
00:04:18,639 --> 00:04:20,359
No, I don't think so.

33
00:04:20,999 --> 00:04:23,479
If we need to wait 10 hours, we wait.

34
00:04:23,559 --> 00:04:26,838
Running at half power, we're not
going to have stability issues?

35
00:04:26,919 --> 00:04:29,438
-No, I should think...
-I'm not asking you.

36
00:04:32,438 --> 00:04:33,639
It's safe.

37
00:04:34,079 --> 00:04:35,439
We'll maintain at 1,600.

38
00:04:35,519 --> 00:04:37,839
I'll go home, get some sleep,
come back tonight.

39
00:04:37,919 --> 00:04:39,119
We'll proceed then.

40
00:04:39,959 --> 00:04:41,959
I'll personally supervise the test.

41
00:04:42,679 --> 00:04:44,398
And it will be completed.

42
00:04:48,119 --> 00:04:49,519
Well, I'm not waiting around, then.

43
00:04:50,799 --> 00:04:52,078
Call me when it's done.

44
00:06:25,679 --> 00:06:26,718
How do you feel?

45
00:06:28,999 --> 00:06:31,478
You went to the doctor yesterday.
How is your health?

46
00:06:32,559 --> 00:06:33,599
You don't know?

47
00:06:35,719 --> 00:06:36,998
From Vienna.

48
00:06:37,278 --> 00:06:38,638
Do you read German?

49
00:06:40,359 --> 00:06:44,999
It says, "At last a Soviet
scientist who tells the truth."

50
00:06:45,638 --> 00:06:47,558
Obviously, I resent the insinuation,

51
00:06:47,639 --> 00:06:48,719
but I think it's fair to say

52
00:06:48,798 --> 00:06:50,998
you made an excellent impression
at the conference.

53
00:06:51,439 --> 00:06:53,399
Turns out, you're quite good at this.

54
00:06:53,919 --> 00:06:55,758
At what? Lying?

55
00:06:55,839 --> 00:06:58,678
Statecraft, Legasov. Statecraft.

56
00:06:58,798 --> 00:07:01,238
The West is now satisfied

57
00:07:01,319 --> 00:07:04,039
that Chernobyl was solely
the result of operator error,

58
00:07:04,118 --> 00:07:05,479
which it essentially was.

59
00:07:06,239 --> 00:07:07,879
We have you to thank for that,

60
00:07:07,958 --> 00:07:09,358
and we intend to.

61
00:07:13,519 --> 00:07:15,479
"Hero of the Soviet Union."

62
00:07:15,918 --> 00:07:17,598
Our highest honor.

63
00:07:17,959 --> 00:07:20,239
They haven't even given it to me.

64
00:07:20,799 --> 00:07:23,878
"Promotion to director
of the Kurchatov Institute."

65
00:07:27,158 --> 00:07:28,438
I'm humbled.

66
00:07:29,039 --> 00:07:32,879
I don't think there's anything humble
about you, Valery Alexeyevich.

67
00:07:32,958 --> 00:07:34,759
These rewards are not yours yet.

68
00:07:35,398 --> 00:07:37,119
First, your testimony at the trial.

69
00:07:37,198 --> 00:07:40,959
Comrade Charkov,
I understand my duty to the State.

70
00:07:42,199 --> 00:07:44,078
But you gave us assurances.

71
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:47,198
The reactors would be made safe.

72
00:07:47,279 --> 00:07:49,639
It's been months.
No changes have been made.

73
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:52,919
-No changes even discussed.
-First, the trial.

74
00:07:54,358 --> 00:07:56,558
Once it's over,
we will have our villains,

75
00:07:56,639 --> 00:07:59,678
we will have our hero,
we will have our truth.

76
00:08:00,559 --> 00:08:03,479
After that,
we can deal with the reactors.

77
00:09:24,919 --> 00:09:26,238
Did you take a train?

78
00:09:26,839 --> 00:09:28,718
Yes, I took a train.

79
00:09:29,599 --> 00:09:31,359
Now let's talk about Vienna.

80
00:09:32,398 --> 00:09:33,959
I'm not here to scold you.

81
00:09:34,598 --> 00:09:37,799
I know how the world works
despite what Shcherbina says.

82
00:09:39,079 --> 00:09:41,838
So, why are you here?

83
00:09:42,998 --> 00:09:44,718
Because I'm brutally stubborn.

84
00:09:45,318 --> 00:09:46,999
Which you were hoping for.

85
00:09:51,279 --> 00:09:54,878
Charkov is saying they're going to fix
the reactors after the trial.

86
00:09:56,838 --> 00:09:58,878
Do you believe him?

87
00:10:01,318 --> 00:10:03,398
The State will never
willingly fix the reactors

88
00:10:03,479 --> 00:10:06,678
because acknowledging the problem
means admitting that they lied.

89
00:10:06,759 --> 00:10:08,399
They will have to be forced.

90
00:10:15,399 --> 00:10:18,399
At the trial,
you're going to tell the truth.

91
00:10:20,238 --> 00:10:22,279
You're going to convince the jury.

92
00:10:22,358 --> 00:10:23,958
It's a show trial.

93
00:10:24,798 --> 00:10:26,519
The jury's already been
handed their verdict.

94
00:10:26,598 --> 00:10:27,879
I'm not talking about them.

95
00:10:30,158 --> 00:10:33,878
The Central Committee have invited
members of the scientific community

96
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:35,318
to observe the trial.

97
00:10:35,839 --> 00:10:38,599
Our colleagues, from Kurchatov,

98
00:10:38,999 --> 00:10:40,998
from Sredmash, from Minenergo,

99
00:10:41,078 --> 00:10:44,518
they will be sitting in the crowd
listening to every word you say.

100
00:10:44,599 --> 00:10:46,718
A jury that only we know is there.

101
00:10:46,799 --> 00:10:50,158
And when your testimony arrives
at the moment of the explosion?

102
00:10:52,118 --> 00:10:55,039
That is when our jury
will finally hear the truth.

103
00:10:55,719 --> 00:10:58,638
-And do what with it?
-Insist on reform.

104
00:11:00,078 --> 00:11:02,358
Not just to the RBMK,
but the entire industry.

105
00:11:02,439 --> 00:11:03,399
<i>No, no, no.</i>

106
00:11:03,478 --> 00:11:04,919
-They can't function without us.
-No,no,no.

107
00:11:04,998 --> 00:11:05,958
If we...

108
00:11:06,038 --> 00:11:09,918
Do you know what happened to Volkov,
the man whose report you found?

109
00:11:10,598 --> 00:11:14,198
They just removed him
from his position at the Institute.

110
00:11:15,079 --> 00:11:17,279
Sacked for the crime of knowing.

111
00:11:18,239 --> 00:11:23,039
And you think that these scientists,
handpicked to witness a show trial,

112
00:11:23,118 --> 00:11:26,198
will somehow be stirred
into action by me?

113
00:11:26,958 --> 00:11:30,318
Because of some heroic stance
I take in defiance of the State?

114
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:31,598
Yes.

115
00:11:31,679 --> 00:11:32,678
Why?

116
00:11:32,759 --> 00:11:36,039
Because you're Valery Legasov,
and you mean something.

117
00:11:38,119 --> 00:11:40,678
I'd like to think that if I spoke out,
it would be enough.

118
00:11:41,918 --> 00:11:43,678
But I know how the world works.

119
00:11:46,918 --> 00:11:49,479
They will shoot me, Khomyuk.

120
00:11:52,878 --> 00:11:55,919
You told me to find out what happened.

121
00:11:55,998 --> 00:11:58,038
I spoke to dozens of people.

122
00:11:58,119 --> 00:12:01,198
Every word they said, I wrote down.

123
00:12:02,399 --> 00:12:03,678
All in these books.

124
00:12:04,878 --> 00:12:06,479
These are the ones
who are still alive.

125
00:12:06,558 --> 00:12:08,118
These are the ones who are dead.

126
00:12:08,198 --> 00:12:09,758
They died rescuing each other.

127
00:12:10,238 --> 00:12:12,959
Putting out fires,
tending to the wounded.

128
00:12:13,038 --> 00:12:14,719
They didn't hesitate.
They didn't waiver.

129
00:12:14,798 --> 00:12:16,799
They simply did what had to be done.

130
00:12:16,878 --> 00:12:17,838
So have I.

131
00:12:19,078 --> 00:12:20,038
So have I.

132
00:12:21,039 --> 00:12:23,079
I went willingly to an open reactor.

133
00:12:23,878 --> 00:12:26,278
So I've already given my life.

134
00:12:27,598 --> 00:12:28,719
Isn't that enough?

135
00:12:30,598 --> 00:12:32,839
No, I'm sorry, but it is not.

