331
00:26:00,558 --> 00:26:02,557
You only need to know this.

332
00:26:02,638 --> 00:26:07,117
There are essentially two things
that happen inside a nuclear reactor.

333
00:26:07,757 --> 00:26:13,318
The reactivity, which generates power,
either goes up or it goes down.

334
00:26:13,957 --> 00:26:14,917
That's it.

335
00:26:15,558 --> 00:26:18,477
All the operators do
is maintain balance.

336
00:26:21,357 --> 00:26:22,477
Uranium fuel.

337
00:26:24,998 --> 00:26:29,518
As uranium atoms split apart
and collide, reactivity goes up.

338
00:26:29,597 --> 00:26:31,477
But if you don't balance
the reactivity,

339
00:26:31,558 --> 00:26:33,478
it never stops rising. So...

340
00:26:35,637 --> 00:26:37,957
Boron control rods.

341
00:26:38,038 --> 00:26:42,517
They reduce reactivity
like brakes on a car.

342
00:26:43,957 --> 00:26:47,518
But there's a third factor
to consider, water.

343
00:26:49,118 --> 00:26:51,557
Cool water takes heat
out of the system.

344
00:26:51,637 --> 00:26:54,837
As it does, it turns to steam,
or what we call a "void."

345
00:26:54,918 --> 00:26:58,198
In an RBMK reactor
of the type used at Chernobyl,

346
00:26:58,277 --> 00:27:01,957
there's something called
a "positive void coefficient."

347
00:27:02,038 --> 00:27:03,157
What does that mean?

348
00:27:03,997 --> 00:27:08,157
It means that the more steam
present within the system,

349
00:27:08,237 --> 00:27:10,238
the higher the reactivity,

350
00:27:10,317 --> 00:27:13,118
which means more heat,
which means more steam,

351
00:27:13,197 --> 00:27:14,157
which means...

352
00:27:15,078 --> 00:27:18,317
It would appear we have
a vicious cycle on our hands.

353
00:27:18,677 --> 00:27:21,317
And we would, were it not for this...

354
00:27:27,197 --> 00:27:32,358
And we would, were it not for this,

355
00:27:32,437 --> 00:27:34,637
the negative temperature coefficient.

356
00:27:35,918 --> 00:27:41,357
When nuclear fuel gets hotter,
it gets less reactive,

357
00:27:42,597 --> 00:27:44,437
so fuel increases reactivity.

358
00:27:45,118 --> 00:27:47,877
Control rods and water reduce it.

359
00:27:47,958 --> 00:27:50,237
Steam increases it,

360
00:27:50,318 --> 00:27:52,677
and the rise in temperature
reduces it.

361
00:27:54,357 --> 00:27:57,077
This is the invisible dance

362
00:27:57,158 --> 00:28:00,677
that powers entire cities
without smoke or flame.

363
00:28:00,757 --> 00:28:02,997
And it is beautiful,

364
00:28:04,038 --> 00:28:05,477
when things are normal.

365
00:28:07,237 --> 00:28:10,038
As uranium splits apart
to release energy,

366
00:28:10,117 --> 00:28:13,397
it breaks down
into a new element, xenon.

367
00:28:13,478 --> 00:28:16,277
Xenon reduces reactivity.

368
00:28:16,358 --> 00:28:18,797
