00:37:20,517 --> 00:37:23,797
Men, material, lunar rovers.

507
00:37:26,517 --> 00:37:28,357
Who else could have done these things?

508
00:37:30,596 --> 00:37:33,037
They heard me,
but they listened to you.

509
00:37:34,197 --> 00:37:37,677
Of all the ministers
and all the deputies,

510
00:37:37,757 --> 00:37:41,237
entire congregation of obedient fools,

511
00:37:42,157 --> 00:37:44,996
they mistakenly sent the one good man.

512
00:37:46,037 --> 00:37:47,957
For God's sakes, Boris,

513
00:37:48,917 --> 00:37:51,237
you were the one who mattered most.

514
00:38:13,437 --> 00:38:15,036
Ah, it's beautiful.

515
00:38:55,356 --> 00:38:57,117
Comrade Legasov.

516
00:39:09,196 --> 00:39:11,157
The time is 38 past midnight.

517
00:39:12,117 --> 00:39:13,876
The reactor is nearly shut down.

518
00:39:14,517 --> 00:39:16,237
The operators of Reactor 4 are locked

519
00:39:16,317 --> 00:39:18,396
on a path that leads
directly to disaster.

520
00:39:18,956 --> 00:39:20,517
There's no way to turn back.

521
00:39:20,917 --> 00:39:23,277
They do not yet know it,
but the die is cast.

522
00:39:24,077 --> 00:39:27,557
At 30 megawatts,
xenon is still being created,

523
00:39:27,637 --> 00:39:29,317
but none of it is burning away.

524
00:39:31,477 --> 00:39:33,317
The reactor is drowning in poison.

525
00:39:34,036 --> 00:39:37,557
To make matters worse,
the reactor isn't hot enough

526
00:39:37,637 --> 00:39:40,117
to produce sufficient steam.

527
00:39:41,996 --> 00:39:44,637
The only way to safely raise
power from this state

528
00:39:44,716 --> 00:39:48,877
is to do it very, very slowly
over the course of 24 hours.

529
00:39:49,637 --> 00:39:51,837
But Dyatlov wants it done now.

530
00:39:52,357 --> 00:39:55,677
Akimov and Toptunov have
only one course of action.

531
00:39:56,557 --> 00:39:58,797
They begin pulling control rods out.

532
00:39:59,437 --> 00:40:00,397
Dozens at a time.

533
00:40:00,877 --> 00:40:03,357
Halfway out,
three-quarters of the way out,

534
00:40:03,437 --> 00:40:06,116
still, the power does not budge.

535
00:40:06,197 --> 00:40:08,797
So they begin pulling
them all the way out.

536
00:40:08,876 --> 00:40:12,517
There were 211 control rods
in Reactor 4.

537
00:40:12,596 --> 00:40:17,076
Akimov and Toptunov
completely withdrew 205.

538
00:40:17,157 --> 00:40:20,997
Remember, control rods
are the brakes on this car.

539
00:40:21,677 --> 00:40:27,916
Of 211 rods, only six
now remain in the reactor.

540
00:40:29,357 --> 00:40:32,036
As for the fuel, it's gone cold,

541
00:40:32,117 --> 00:40:34,037
so the negative
temperature coefficient

542
00:40:34,116 --> 00:40:36,596
is no longer
weighing down the reactivity.

543
00:40:36,677 --> 00:40:40,396
But even still,
the xenon poisoning is so strong,

544
00:40:40,477 --> 00:40:43,917
the best they can do is raise
the power to 200 megawatts.

545
00:40:45,277 --> 00:40:46,996
The control rods are out.

546
00:40:47,436 --> 00:40:49,797
The emergency system
has been disconnected.

547
00:40:49,876 --> 00:40:51,956
The only thing keeping
the reactor in check

548
00:40:52,037 --> 00:40:54,516
is water and xenon.

549
00:40:54,597 --> 00:40:58,356
It's 1:00 in the morning.
The test is minutes away.

550
00:41:31,477 --> 00:41:33,516
I'm sorry, this is all we can get.

551
00:41:33,997 --> 00:41:36,317
It's 200 megawatts.
We've pulled almost everything out.

552
00:41:36,877 --> 00:41:38,276
If that's all we have,
that's all we have.

553
00:41:38,716 --> 00:41:42,116
-But the test requires 700.
-Stolyarchuk, let's get ready.

554
00:41:42,197 --> 00:41:43,796
- Switch on pump four.
- No, wait a second.

555
00:41:43,877 --> 00:41:45,757
- Stolyarchuk...
- We have barely enough steam as it is.

556
00:41:45,836 --> 00:41:48,156
The turbine is going too slow for
the test to deliver any valid results.

557
00:41:48,237 --> 00:41:49,556
-It's enough.
-And if we add more water,

558
00:41:49,637 --> 00:41:51,237
-there will be even less...
-I said it's enough.

559
00:41:51,316 --> 00:41:52,436
I know what I'm doing. Stolyarchuk.

560
00:41:58,517 --> 00:41:59,836
Main pump four, connected.

561
00:42:00,197 --> 00:42:01,837
We should warn Khodemchuk.
The pipes are gonna be...

562
00:42:01,916 --> 00:42:03,357
Never mind him. Kirschenbaum?

563
00:42:06,597 --> 00:42:09,197
The steam in the separator drum
is too low, five atmospheres.

564
00:42:09,276 --> 00:42:11,876
All right, let's all help him.
Get it up as best you can.

565
00:42:15,996 --> 00:42:17,037
We should stop.

566
00:42:17,676 --> 00:42:19,276
Turn that fucking thing off.

567
00:42:20,396 --> 00:42:21,957
You have 15 minutes.

568
00:42:23,757 --> 00:42:24,877
<i>Fifteen minutes.</i>

569
00:42:26,077 --> 00:42:28,397
<i>They may as well have had 15 days.</i>

570
00:42:28,717 --> 00:42:31,356
The problem they were facing
was not solvable.

571
00:42:31,437 --> 00:42:33,956
The power was too low.
The water was too high.

572
00:42:34,037 --> 00:42:35,596
The test was already ruined.

573
00:42:35,677 --> 00:42:38,516
The results would have been useless,
but Dyatlov didn't care.

574
00:42:38,916 --> 00:42:41,516
All he wanted to do was
report a completed test.

575
00:42:42,916 --> 00:42:44,956
<i>1:22 am.</i>

576
00:42:45,636 --> 00:42:47,436
<i>Less than two minutes remain.</i>

577
00:42:48,636 --> 00:42:52,437
<i>Yuvchenko, a mechanical engineer,
is in his office.</i>

578
00:42:56,476 --> 00:42:58,757
<i>Perevozchenko,
reactor section foreman,</i>

579
00:42:58,836 --> 00:42:59,957
<i>is in the refueling hall,</i>

580
00:43:00,517 --> 00:43:03,957
<i>high above the 1,000—ton
steel reactor cover.</i>

581
00:43:06,277 --> 00:43:08,197
<i>Degtaryenko, Khodemchuk,</i>

582
00:43:08,276 --> 00:43:10,957
<i>circulation operators,
are in the pump room.</i>

583
00:43:13,117 --> 00:43:16,236
None of them
have been told about the test.

584
00:43:16,317 --> 00:43:18,077
None of them know
what is about to happen.

585
00:43:18,836 --> 00:43:23,677
<i>At 1:22 and 30 seconds,
Toptunov sees a report</i>

586
00:43:24,517 --> 00:43:27,237
<i>from the reactor's
SKALA computer system.</i>

587
00:43:28,396 --> 00:43:31,596
<i>Based on the absence
of sufficient control rods,</i>

588
00:43:31,677 --> 00:43:34,716
<i>the computer is recommending
that the reactor be shut down.</i>

589
00:43:40,396 --> 00:43:42,757
Well, of course it's saying that.
It doesn't know we're running a test.

590
00:43:44,837 --> 00:43:45,876
All right, comrades.

591
00:43:47,636 --> 00:43:50,037
Another few minutes,
it will all be over.

592
00:43:50,116 --> 00:43:51,436
Kirschenbaum, when you're ready.

593
00:43:52,716 --> 00:43:53,757
We did everything right.

594
00:43:56,156 --> 00:43:57,597
Oscillograph on.

595
00:43:59,556 --> 00:44:01,157
Closing number eight throttle valve.

596
00:44:02,237 --> 00:44:03,716
Generator rotor
beginning rundown.

597
00:44:04,157 --> 00:44:06,757
<i>1:23 and four seconds.</i>

598
00:44:07,556 --> 00:44:11,277
With every decision, they have pulled
this reactor back like a slingshot,

599
00:44:11,356 --> 00:44:13,316
further than anyone has ever pulled.

600
00:44:13,877 --> 00:44:15,397
Now the test begins.

601
00:44:15,916 --> 00:44:18,756
The pumps are shut down,
and they've let go.

602
00:44:21,756 --> 00:44:24,396
The pumps stop moving water
through the reactor.

603
00:44:25,036 --> 00:44:27,996
Uranium fuel is now
unchecked by fresh coolant,

604
00:44:28,076 --> 00:44:29,957
unchecked by control rods.

605
00:44:30,036 --> 00:44:32,916
The balance immediately swings
in the opposite direction.

606
00:44:32,996 --> 00:44:35,997
In less than a second,
reactivity increases.

607
00:44:37,276 --> 00:44:38,636
<i>Inside the core,</i>

608
00:44:38,717 --> 00:44:40,956
<i>the remaining water is
quickly converting to steam.</i>

609
00:44:41,037 --> 00:44:43,117
<i>A void is being created.</i>

610
00:44:43,196 --> 00:44:45,636
<i>There is no fresh water to replace it.</i>

611
00:44:45,717 --> 00:44:48,516
Steam increases reactivity,

612
00:44:48,597 --> 00:44:51,757
increases heat, increases steam,

613
00:44:51,836 --> 00:44:53,397
increases reactivity.

614
00:44:54,637 --> 00:44:57,556
The remaining xenon decays away.

615
00:44:58,916 --> 00:45:00,356
The power is rising.

616
00:45:02,556 --> 00:45:03,996
There's nothing left to stop it.

617
00:45:05,317 --> 00:45:08,596
<i>1:23 and 35 seconds.</i>

618
00:45:11,796 --> 00:45:13,796
We have a power surge! Sasha!

619
00:45:19,076 --> 00:45:20,157
What did you do?

620
00:45:20,716 --> 00:45:23,796
1:23 and 40 seconds.

621
00:45:31,677 --> 00:45:34,076
In every control room
of every nuclear reactor in the world,

622
00:45:34,156 --> 00:45:37,196
there is a button
with one single purpose,

623
00:45:37,277 --> 00:45:40,556
to "scram," or instantly
shut down the reaction.

624
00:45:40,636 --> 00:45:43,756
In Soviet reactors,
that button is called AZ-5.

625
00:45:44,636 --> 00:45:46,597
You press AZ-5,

626
00:45:46,676 --> 00:45:48,797
all of the control rods
insert at once,

627
00:45:48,876 --> 00:45:52,276
and the reaction is stopped dead.

628
00:45:53,317 --> 00:45:54,437
But...

629
00:46:00,716 --> 00:46:01,957
What are you waiting for, Legasov?

630
00:46:02,036 --> 00:46:03,877
Tell your lies.

631
00:46:03,956 --> 00:46:06,077
Comrade Dyatlov,
you will not be warned again.

632
00:46:06,156 --> 00:46:08,277
- Or what?
- For God's sake, Dyatlov.

633
00:46:08,356 --> 00:46:10,276
-Legasov's already given it away.
-That's enough.

634
00:46:10,356 --> 00:46:13,276
He said before there was no way
to avoid What was coming.

635
00:46:13,357 --> 00:46:14,916
-He knows something.
-Comrade Dyatlov.

636
00:46:14,997 --> 00:46:16,517
She knows something.

637
00:46:17,757 --> 00:46:19,716
I know what you are,
Valery Alexeyevich.

638
00:46:19,797 --> 00:46:22,677
-You're a liar.
-We've heard enough for today.

639
00:46:23,796 --> 00:46:26,397
The defendants will be
remanded in custody.

640
00:46:26,476 --> 00:46:29,356
-Court will...
-I haven't finished.

641
00:46:29,436 --> 00:46:31,476
I still have more evidence to give.

642
00:46:31,556 --> 00:46:34,716
It's not necessary.
Your testimony is concluded.

643
00:46:34,796 --> 00:46:37,836
-Your Honor.
-Court is now adjourned.

644
00:46:37,917 --> 00:46:40,036
- We will resume tomorrow with...
- Let him finish.

645
00:46:42,636 --> 00:46:43,916
Comrade Shcherbina...

646
00:46:46,557 --> 00:46:47,556
Let him finish.

647
00:47:11,796 --> 00:47:14,036
Dyatlov broke every rule we have.

648
00:47:17,596 --> 00:47:20,596
He pushed a reactor
to the brink of destruction.

649
00:47:24,957 --> 00:47:27,436
He did these things believing
there was a fail safe.

650
00:47:27,516 --> 00:47:30,837
AZ-5, a simple button
to shut it all down.

651
00:47:30,916 --> 00:47:35,276
But in the circumstances he created,
there wasn't.

652
00:47:35,356 --> 00:47:38,436
The shutdown system had a fatal flaw.

653
00:47:40,476 --> 00:47:45,517
At 1:23:40, Akimov engages AZ-5.

654
00:47:53,236 --> 00:47:56,876
The fully withdrawn control rods
begin moving back into the reactor.

655
00:47:56,956 --> 00:47:59,517
These rods are made of boron,
which reduces reactivity,

656
00:47:59,596 --> 00:48:00,636
but not their tips.

657
00:48:01,437 --> 00:48:05,556
The tips are made of graphite,
which accelerates reactivity.

658
00:48:06,036 --> 00:48:06,996
Why?

659
00:48:11,476 --> 00:48:12,556
Why?

660
00:48:15,076 --> 00:48:17,276
For the same reason our reactors

661
00:48:17,356 --> 00:48:19,356
do not have containment
buildings around them,

662
00:48:20,276 --> 00:48:21,356
like those in the West.

663
00:48:21,436 --> 00:48:25,956
For the same reason we don't use
properly enriched fuel in our cores.

664
00:48:26,196 --> 00:48:28,436
For the same reason
we are the only nation

665
00:48:28,516 --> 00:48:32,676
that builds water-cooled,
graphite-moderated reactors

666
00:48:32,756 --> 00:48:35,116
with a positive void coefficient.

667
00:48:36,916 --> 00:48:37,917
It's cheaper.

668
00:48:43,876 --> 00:48:45,076
The first part

669
00:48:45,156 --> 00:48:46,876
of the rods that enter the core

670
00:48:46,956 --> 00:48:48,236
are the graphite tips.

671
00:48:48,316 --> 00:48:50,556
And when they do,
the reaction in the core,

672
00:48:50,636 --> 00:48:53,396
which had been rising, skyrockets.

673
00:48:53,476 --> 00:48:58,276
Every last molecule of liquid water
instantly converts to steam,

674
00:48:58,356 --> 00:49:01,516
which expands and ruptures
a series of fuel rod channels.

675
00:49:01,596 --> 00:49:05,516
The control rods in those
channels can move no further.

676
00:49:05,596 --> 00:49:07,956
The graphite tips
are fixed in position,

677
00:49:08,036 --> 00:49:10,796
endlessly accelerating the reaction.

678
00:49:10,876 --> 00:49:14,556
Chernobyl Reactor 4
is now a nuclear bomb.

679
00:49:15,076 --> 00:49:17,516
<i>1:23:42.</i>

680
00:49:17,596 --> 00:49:21,396
<i>Perevozchenko looks down on
the enormous steel lid of the reactor</i>

681
00:49:21,476 --> 00:49:23,396
<i>and sees the impossible.</i>

682
00:49:23,476 --> 00:49:25,196
<i>The control rod and fuel channel caps,</i>

683
00:49:25,276 --> 00:49:27,276
<i>which each weigh 350 kilograms,</i>

684
00:49:27,356 --> 00:49:28,956
<i>are jumping up and down.</i>

685
00:49:29,476 --> 00:49:31,596
<i>He runs to warn the control room.</i>

686
00:49:31,677 --> 00:49:34,476
<i>But there's nothing he can do
to stop what is coming.</i>

687
00:49:34,557 --> 00:49:37,437
<i>1:23</i> and 44 <i>seconds.</i>

688
00:49:38,036 --> 00:49:41,316
<i>The steam blows
more fuel channels apart.</i>

689
00:49:41,396 --> 00:49:43,356
<i>We do not know
how high the power went.</i>

690
00:49:43,436 --> 00:49:44,596
<i>We only know the final reading.</i>

691
00:49:47,076 --> 00:49:51,436
Reactor 4, designed to operate
at 3,200 megawatts,

692
00:49:52,156 --> 00:49:54,596
went beyond 33,000.

693
00:50:00,116 --> 00:50:03,756
The pressure inside the core
can no longer be held back.

694
00:50:03,836 --> 00:50:09,876
At long last, we have arrived.
1:23:45, explosion.

695
00:50:11,436 --> 00:50:14,276
<i>In the instant the lid is
thrown off the reactor,</i>

696
00:50:14,356 --> 00:50:15,356
<i>oxygen rushes in.</i>

697
00:50:15,436 --> 00:50:19,356
<i>It combines with hydrogen
and super-heated graphite.</i>

698
00:50:21,316 --> 00:50:24,036
<i>The chain of disaster is now complete.</i>

699
00:50:45,276 --> 00:50:46,636
Comrade Dyatlov!

700
00:50:51,676 --> 00:50:52,956
Comrade Dyatlov!

701
00:51:03,996 --> 00:51:06,756
No one in the room
that night knew

702
00:51:06,836 --> 00:51:09,875
the shutdown button
could act as a detonator.

703
00:51:11,436 --> 00:51:12,716
They didn't know it,

704
00:51:14,316 --> 00:51:16,236
because it was kept from them.

705
00:51:16,316 --> 00:51:20,876
Comrade Legasov, you're contradicting
your own testimony in Vienna.

706
00:51:21,276 --> 00:51:23,156
My testimony in Vienna was a lie.

707
00:51:24,596 --> 00:51:26,796
I lied to the world.

708
00:51:27,596 --> 00:51:29,356
I'm not the only one
who kept this secret.

709
00:51:29,436 --> 00:51:30,396
There are many.

710
00:51:31,916 --> 00:51:33,276
We were following orders,

711
00:51:34,796 --> 00:51:36,356
from the KGB,
from the Central Committee.

712
00:51:36,436 --> 00:51:38,876
And right now, there are
16 reactors in the Soviet Union

713
00:51:38,956 --> 00:51:41,316
with the same fatal flaw.

714
00:51:41,396 --> 00:51:43,196
Three of them are still running

715
00:51:43,276 --> 00:51:45,596
less than 20 kilometers away
at Chernobyl.

716
00:51:45,675 --> 00:51:49,436
Professor Legasov, if you mean
to suggest the Soviet state

717
00:51:49,515 --> 00:51:51,276
is somehow responsible
for what happened,

718
00:51:51,356 --> 00:51:53,956
then I must warn you, you are
treading on dangerous ground.

