00:55:50,596 --> 00:55:52,876
In a just world,
I'd be shot for my lies,

752
00:55:52,955 --> 00:55:55,076
but not for this, not for the truth.

753
00:55:55,995 --> 00:55:58,076
Scientists,

754
00:55:58,155 --> 00:56:01,715
and your idiot obsession
with reasons.

755
00:56:01,796 --> 00:56:06,036
When the bullet hits
your skull, what will it matter why?

756
00:56:13,395 --> 00:56:15,636
No one's getting shot, Legasov.

757
00:56:17,276 --> 00:56:18,875
The whole world saw you in Vienna.

758
00:56:19,676 --> 00:56:21,676
It would be embarrassing
to kill you now.

759
00:56:21,755 --> 00:56:22,756
And for what?

760
00:56:24,075 --> 00:56:26,995
Your testimony today
will not be accepted by the State.

761
00:56:27,076 --> 00:56:29,315
It will not be disseminated
in the press.

762
00:56:29,956 --> 00:56:31,716
It never happened.

763
00:56:33,036 --> 00:56:37,115
No, you will live,
however long you have,

764
00:56:37,876 --> 00:56:40,516
but not as a scientist, not anymore.

765
00:56:41,476 --> 00:56:45,276
You'll keep your title
and your office,

766
00:56:46,435 --> 00:56:50,596
but no duties,
no authority, no friends.

767
00:56:50,675 --> 00:56:51,955
No one will talk to you.

768
00:56:52,755 --> 00:56:54,076
No one will listen to you.

769
00:56:56,435 --> 00:56:59,716
Other men, lesser men,

770
00:57:00,796 --> 00:57:03,396
will receive credit
for the things you have done.

771
00:57:04,316 --> 00:57:06,516
Your legacy is now their legacy.

772
00:57:06,595 --> 00:57:08,716
You'll live long enough to see that.

773
00:57:12,515 --> 00:57:14,275
What role did Shcherbina play in this?

774
00:57:14,995 --> 00:57:16,036
None.

775
00:57:16,116 --> 00:57:17,875
He didn't know what I was gonna say.

776
00:57:19,716 --> 00:57:21,715
What role did Khomyuk play in this?

777
00:57:22,355 --> 00:57:23,315
None.

778
00:57:24,155 --> 00:57:25,515
She didn't know either.

779
00:57:27,956 --> 00:57:30,315
After all you've said and done today,

780
00:57:30,396 --> 00:57:35,795
it would be curious
if you chose this moment to lie.

781
00:57:38,876 --> 00:57:42,716
I would think a man of your experience
would know a lie when he hears one.

782
00:57:46,876 --> 00:57:49,756
You will not meet or communicate
with either one of them ever again.

783
00:57:51,195 --> 00:57:54,516
You will not communicate with anyone
about Chernobyl ever again.

784
00:57:55,955 --> 00:57:58,116
You will remain so immaterial
to the world around you

785
00:57:58,195 --> 00:57:59,996
that when you finally do die,

786
00:58:00,596 --> 00:58:04,036
it will be exceedingly hard
to know that you ever lived at all.

787
00:58:08,315 --> 00:58:09,955
And if I refuse?

788
00:58:13,196 --> 00:58:15,995
Why worry about something
that isn't going to happen?

789
00:58:17,355 --> 00:58:20,436
"Why worry about something
that isn't going to happen?"

790
00:58:21,355 --> 00:58:22,835
Oh, that's perfect.

791
00:58:23,675 --> 00:58:25,436
They should put that on our money.

792
00:59:32,996 --> 00:59:35,636
<i><i>To be a scientist is to be naive.</i>

793
00:59:36,915 --> 00:59:39,155
<i>We are so focused
on our search for truth,</i>

794
00:59:39,235 --> 00:59:43,235
<i>we fail to consider how few
actually want us to find it.</i>

795
00:59:43,755 --> 00:59:47,795
<i>But it is always there,
whether we see it or not,</i>

796
00:59:47,875 --> 00:59:49,756
<i>whether we choose to or not.</i>

797
00:59:49,835 --> 00:59:52,435
<i>The truth doesn't care
about our needs or wants.</i>

798
00:59:52,516 --> 00:59:54,116
<i>It doesn't care about our governments,</i>

799
00:59:54,195 --> 00:59:56,435
<i>our ideologies, our religions.</i>

800
00:59:57,836 --> 01:00:00,196
<i>It will lie in wait for all time.</i>

801
01:00:01,436 --> 01:00:05,195
<i>And this, at last,
is the gift of Chernobyl.</i>

802
01:00:05,276 --> 01:00:07,635
<i>Where I once would fear
the cost of truth,</i>

803
01:00:07,716 --> 01:00:09,275
<i>now I only ask,</i>

804
01:00:11,355 --> 01:00:13,235
<i>"What is the cost of lies?"</i>

